    <h3>How to Reduce Refrigeration Electricity Costs</h3>

    <ol>
      <li><strong>Buy higher star-rated units.</strong> The upfront premium of 10–15% pays back in 2–3 years.</li>
      <li><strong>Keep the condenser coils clean.</strong> Dusty coils make the compressor work 15–25% harder.</li>
      <li><strong>Maintain door gaskets.</strong> A worn gasket leaks cold air continuously — replacement costs only ₹500–₹1,500 but can save ₹200–₹400/month in electricity.</li>
      <li><strong>Don't place the fridge near heat sources.</strong> Keep it away from ovens, direct sunlight, and exhaust vents. Every 1°C increase in ambient temperature raises consumption by approximately 2–3%.</li>
      <li><strong>Set the correct temperature.</strong> Running a fridge at 2°C when you only need 5°C wastes energy. Each degree lower uses about 5% more electricity.</li>
      <li><strong>Install strip curtains on walk-in coolers.</strong> A ₹2,000 strip curtain can reduce cold air loss by 30–50% when the door is opened.</li>
      <li><strong>Use night covers on open display units.</strong> If you have open-front display chillers (multi-deck), always use the night blinds when the shop is closed.</li>
    </ol>

    <p>For a complete picture of operating costs in a bakery, including refrigeration, see our <a href="/blog/bakery-setup-cost-india">bakery setup cost</a> breakdown.</p>

