    <h2 id="installation-tips">Installation Best Practices</h2>

    <p>Proper installation is just as important as buying the right unit. Poor installation leads to premature failures and higher energy costs.</p>

    <h3>Clearance Requirements</h3>
    <p>Every commercial fridge needs adequate clearance around the condenser for heat dissipation. As a general rule:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Rear-mounted condenser:</strong> Minimum 10–15 cm clearance from the wall</li>
      <li><strong>Top-mounted condenser:</strong> Minimum 30 cm clearance above the unit</li>
      <li><strong>Bottom-mounted condenser:</strong> Keep the floor clean — no boxes or debris blocking airflow</li>
      <li><strong>Side clearance:</strong> At least 5 cm on each side for multi-unit installations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Electrical Requirements</h3>
    <p>Most commercial fridges in India run on single-phase 220V supply. Larger units (walk-in coolers, 4-door vertical refrigerators) may require three-phase 440V supply. Always verify the electrical requirements before purchase and ensure your shop's wiring can handle the load.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Install a dedicated electrical circuit for each large commercial fridge</li>
      <li>Use a voltage stabilizer (especially in areas with frequent power fluctuations)</li>
      <li>Install an MCB (miniature circuit breaker) of the correct rating for each unit</li>
      <li>Avoid extension cords — always use a wall socket with proper earthing</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Flooring and Levelling</h3>
    <p>Commercial fridges are heavy (a 2-door vertical chiller weighs 120–180 kg). Ensure the floor can support the weight. Tile or concrete flooring is ideal. If using castor wheels, lock them once the unit is positioned. Use a spirit level to ensure the unit is perfectly level — an unlevel fridge causes door seal issues and uneven cooling.</p>

    <h2 id="commercial-vs-domestic">Commercial vs. Domestic Fridge — Why You Can't Use a Home Fridge in Your Shop</h2>

    <p>We frequently get asked: "Can I use a large domestic fridge for my shop to save money?" The short answer is no, and here's why:</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Domestic Fridge</th><th>Commercial Fridge</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Door openings per day</td><td>Designed for 10–20</td><td>Designed for 50–200+</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Temperature recovery</td><td>15–30 minutes</td><td>3–8 minutes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ambient temperature rating</td><td>Up to 38°C</td><td>Up to 43°C (tropicalized)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor duty cycle</td><td>Light duty</td><td>Heavy duty (continuous run)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Build material</td><td>Plastic interior</td><td>Stainless steel interior</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty for commercial use</td><td>Void</td><td>Valid</td></tr>
        <tr><td>FSSAI compliance</td><td>Not rated</td><td>Compliant</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Expected lifespan (commercial use)</td><td>2–3 years</td><td>10–15 years</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>A domestic fridge used commercially will fail within 2–3 years, void its warranty, and potentially cause food safety issues. The "savings" are an illusion — you'll spend more in the long run on replacements and spoiled inventory.</p>

    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>What is the price of a commercial fridge for a small shop in India?</h3>
    <p>For a small shop (kirana, juice bar, or small bakery), you can get a functional commercial fridge starting at ₹12,000–₹15,000 for a 120L visi cooler. A more practical 300–350L visi cooler costs ₹20,000–₹33,000. If you need a deep freezer, budget ₹14,000–₹28,000 for a 100–200L unit. Total budget for basic refrigeration in a small shop: ₹25,000–₹60,000.</p>

    <h3>Which brand is best for commercial refrigerator in India?</h3>
    <p>Blue Star offers the best combination of product range, quality, and after-sales service network across India. For deep freezers specifically, Western Refrigeration offers the best value. For professional kitchen equipment (under-counter units, reach-in chillers), Elanpro and Celfrost are top choices. Voltas and Godrej are solid options in the mid-range segment with wide availability.</p>

    <h3>How much electricity does a commercial fridge consume per month?</h3>
    <p>A single-door 300L visi cooler consumes approximately 90–135 units (kWh) per month, costing ₹720–₹1,080 at ₹8/kWh. A two-door vertical chiller (1,000L) consumes 180–270 units per month, costing ₹1,440–₹2,160. Deep freezers (400L) consume 120–180 units monthly, costing ₹960–₹1,440. Exact consumption depends on star rating, ambient temperature, door opening frequency, and loading pattern.</p>

    <h3>Is a glass door refrigerator commercial unit better than a solid door one?</h3>
    <p>For front-of-house display purposes, a <strong>glass door refrigerator commercial</strong> unit is significantly better — customers can see products without opening the door, which drives impulse purchases and reduces cold air loss. However, glass doors provide slightly less insulation than solid doors, meaning marginally higher electricity consumption. For back-of-house storage where display isn't needed, solid stainless steel doors are more efficient, more durable, and cheaper. Many shops use glass-door units up front and solid-door units in the kitchen.</p>

    <h3>Can I get a commercial fridge on EMI or loan?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Most major dealers offer EMI through Bajaj Finance, ZestMoney, or Capital Float with 6–12 month terms. Banks offer equipment loans at 10–14% interest for larger purchases. Government MUDRA loans (Shishu up to ₹5 lakh, Kishore up to ₹10 lakh) are available for small business owners at subsidized rates. BakeDesk can help connect you with financing partners — see our <a href="/blog/bakery-equipment-financing">equipment financing</a> guide for details.</p>

    <h3>What size commercial fridge do I need for my restaurant?</h3>
    <p>For a restaurant serving 100–150 covers per day, plan for at least 800–1,200L of chiller space (a two-door vertical chiller) plus 200–300L of freezer space. Add an under-counter unit at each prep station (150–300L each). For 200+ covers, you'll need 1,500L+ of chiller space (three-door vertical) and 400L+ of freezer. Always calculate at 60–70% loading capacity — a 1,000L fridge effectively stores about 650L of product for proper airflow.</p>

    <h3>How often should a commercial fridge be serviced?</h3>
    <p>Monthly: Clean condenser coils and check door gaskets. Quarterly: Verify temperature accuracy with an independent thermometer, clean drain lines, and inspect fan motors. Annually: Full professional service including refrigerant pressure check, compressor current draw test, and electrical connection inspection. Budget ₹1,500–₹3,000 per unit per year for professional servicing.</p>

    <h3>What is the warranty on commercial fridges in India?</h3>
    <p>Most brands offer 1 year comprehensive warranty (covering all parts and labour) plus 4–5 years additional warranty on the compressor. Blue Star, Voltas, and Godrej offer 5-year compressor warranty as standard. Some brands (Elanpro, Celfrost) offer extended warranty packages at additional cost. Always register your product warranty online within 15 days of purchase to avoid disputes later.</p>

